The paper discusses the use of Autoencoders in Collaborative Filtering recommender systems, which is a common application of Deep Learning in the field of Information Retrieval (IR) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). The paper also focuses on the explainability of the Autoencoder-based recommender system, which is a current topic of interest in the field of Machine Learning (ML) and Natural Language Processing (NLP), falling under the sub-categories of Language and Vision (cs.CL) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). Overall, the paper's content and focus suggest that it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
